%description:
Deterministic MLDv1 router/querier group-state-transition test (RFC 2710 §6).

Exercises the three querier group states across two trajectories, proved by
Mldv1 EV_INFO markers in stdout.  Membership is driven by real apps (UdpSink
with multicastGroup), the production path.

RFC 2710 §6 router group state machine (simplified):
  No Listeners Present
    |  Report received (record listener, start multicast-listener timer)
    v
  Listeners Present  <--- Report received (refresh timer)
    |  Done received (send MAS Query, start leave timer, start rexmt timer)
    v
  Checking Listeners  <--- rexmt timer expired (send MAS Query, restart rexmt)
    |  leave timer expired (remove group) -- EV_DEBUG only
    v
  No Listeners Present

Trajectories tested:

TRAJ-1  ff0e::1  (leave-driven removal)
  host1 runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::1" and stopTime=5s.
  At t=0 the socket join fires -> unsolicited Report sent -> router records listener
  (No Listeners Present --> Listeners Present).
  At t=5s the socket close fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal -> Done sent to ff02::2.
  Router receives Done -> sends Multicast-Address-Specific Query
  (Listeners Present --> Checking Listeners), starts leave timer and rexmt timer.
  rexmt timer fires at t~6s -> second MAS Query sent (proves Checking Listeners
  countdown is running). Leave timer fires at t~7s -> group removed (EV_DEBUG only,
  asserted indirectly: no "recorded listener for group=ff0e::1" after t=7s in a
  %not-contains on the post-rexmt window).

TRAJ-2  ff0e::2  (leave-free multicast-listener-interval timeout)
  host2 runs UdpSink with multicastGroup="ff0e::2" (no stopTime -- persistent listener).
  At t=0 the socket join fires -> unsolicited Report -> router records listener.
  No Done is sent; multicastListenerInterval=10s fires at t~10s -> leave timer
  expires -> group removed (EV_DEBUG only). The absence of ff0e::2 from any
  MAS Query proves the router never entered Checking Listeners for this group
  (it went directly to No Listeners Present via timer expiry).

SINGLE-QUERIER PROOF:
  host1 and host2 have multicastForwarding=false (the default). Only the router
  runs the querier path. A %postrun-command extracts any Query-sending lines from
  host1/host2 and a %not-contains asserts the list is empty.

Network: host1, host2, and router connect to a shared EthernetHub.
Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator assigns addresses. hasMld=true on all nodes.
dupAddrDetectTransmits=0 eliminates DAD delay. seed-set=0 pins RNG.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.networklayer.configurator.ipv6.Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
import inet.node.ethernet.EthernetHub;
import inet.node.ipv6.Router6;
import inet.node.ipv6.StandardHost6;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork
{
    types:
        channel ethline extends DatarateChannel
        {
            delay = 0.1us;
            datarate = 100Mbps;
        }
    submodules:
        configurator: Ipv6FlatNetworkConfigurator;
        host1: StandardHost6;
        host2: StandardHost6;
        router: Router6;
        hub: EthernetHub;
    connections:
        host1.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        host2.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
        router.ethg++ <--> ethline <--> hub.ethg++;
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = ../../../../src
network = MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork
sim-time-limit = 20s
cmdenv-express-mode = false
cmdenv-log-prefix = "%C: "

# Fix RNG seed for deterministic behavior of uniform(0, maxRespTime) in startHostTimer
seed-set = 0

eventlog-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.elog"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sca"
output-vector-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.vec"
snapshot-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-${runnumber}.sna"

# Enable MLD on all nodes so hosts can receive router Queries and router can receive Reports/Dones
**.ipv6.hasMld = true
# Disable DAD for fast startup (no ~1s delay before addresses become ready)
**.neighbourDiscovery.dupAddrDetectTransmits = 0

**.eth[*].queue.typename = "EthernetQosQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.eth[*].queue.dataQueue.packetCapacity = 10

# Activate the real querier ONLY on the router.
# Must be set at the node (Router6) level: NetworkLayerNodeBase propagates
#   *.multicastForwarding = this.multicastForwarding
# to all submodules (including ipv6.routingTable), overriding any per-submodule INI setting.
**.router.multicastForwarding = true

# Router timer settings:
# startupQueryInterval=1s: first General Query fires shortly after init (not the focus here)
**.router.ipv6.mld.startupQueryInterval = 1s
# queryInterval=100s: long so periodic General Queries do not interfere with per-group trajectories
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryInterval = 100s
**.router.ipv6.mld.queryResponseInterval = 1s
# lastListenerQueryInterval=1s, lastListenerQueryCount=2: leave timer = 2s, rexmt fires at 1s
# This allows observing both the Done-triggered MAS Query and the rexmt MAS Query within sim time.
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryInterval = 1s
**.router.ipv6.mld.lastListenerQueryCount = 2
# multicastListenerInterval=10s: short so TRAJ-2 (ff0e::2, no Done) ages out by t~10s within 20s sim
**.router.ipv6.mld.multicastListenerInterval = 10s

# TRAJ-1: host1 joins ff0e::1 via UdpSink (fires ipv6MulticastGroupJoinedSignal -> unsolicited Report).
# host1 leaves at t=5s via socket close (fires ipv6MulticastGroupLeftSignal -> Done).
**.host1.numApps = 1
**.host1.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host1.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host1.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::1"
**.host1.app[0].stopTime = 5s

# TRAJ-2: host2 joins ff0e::2; no leave -- group ages out via multicastListenerInterval.
**.host2.numApps = 1
**.host2.app[0].typename = "UdpSink"
**.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000
**.host2.app[0].multicastGroup = "ff0e::2"

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%subst: /omnetpp:://
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-1 RTR-02: router receives host1's unsolicited Report for ff0e::1
%# Proves: No Listeners Present - router sees the Report
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::1 iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-1 RTR-02: router records the listener (No Listeners Present --> Listeners Present)
%# "recorded listener" is only emitted on the FIRST recording (not on timer refresh)
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: recorded listener for group=ff0e::1

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-1 RTR-03: router receives host1's Done for ff0e::1 (from socket close at t=5s)
%# Proves: Listeners Present state was active (Done only matters when a listener was present)
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Done for group=ff0e::1 iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-1 RTR-03: router sends Multicast-Address-Specific Query on receiving the Done
%# Proves: Listeners Present --> Checking Listeners transition
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1 on iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-2 RTR-02: router receives host2's unsolicited Report for ff0e::2
%# Proves: No Listeners Present for ff0e::2 - router sees the Report
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: received Multicast Listener Report for group=ff0e::2 iface=

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-2 RTR-02: router records listener for ff0e::2 (No Listeners Present --> Listeners Present)
%contains: stdout
MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: recorded listener for group=ff0e::2

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-1 indirect No-Listeners-Present proof: rexmt timer fires a second MAS Query for ff0e::1.
%# lastListenerQueryCount=2 means the router sends MAS Query twice: once on receiving the Done
%# (Listeners Present --> Checking Listeners) and once more when the rexmt timer fires.
%# Extract the 2nd MAS Query line via sed -n '2p'; a non-empty result proves the rexmt path
%# actually ran.  If the rexmt were broken, only 1 MAS Query would be sent and the output file
%# would be empty, causing %contains to fail.
%postrun-command: grep "MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1" test.out | sed -n '2p' > mas_query_ff0e1_rexmt.out || true
%contains: mas_query_ff0e1_rexmt.out
Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::1

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# TRAJ-2 indirect No-Listeners-Present proof: ff0e::2 never triggers a Done so the router
%# should NEVER send a MAS Query for it (it goes directly to No Listeners Present via timer expiry).
%postrun-command: grep "MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork.router.ipv6.mld: Mldv1: sending Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::2" test.out > mas_query_ff0e2.out || true
%not-contains: mas_query_ff0e2.out
Multicast-Address-Specific Query for group=ff0e::2

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# SINGLE-QUERIER PROOF: host1 and host2 have multicastForwarding=false (the default) and
%# must NEVER send any Query. Extract all host Query-sending lines; the file must be empty.
%postrun-command: grep -E "MldQuerierGroupstatesNetwork\.(host1|host2)\.ipv6\.mld: Mldv1: sending (General Listener|Multicast-Address-Specific) Query" test.out > host_query.out || true
%not-contains: host_query.out
Query

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Undisposed-object guard: verify no leaked cMessage or cObject at end of run
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
